.TH "ldm_validate_tocblocks" 9 "ldm_validate_tocblocks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ldm_validate_tocblocks \- Validate the table of contents and its backups
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" ldm_validate_tocblocks
.BI "(struct parsed_partitions *state "  ","
.BI "unsigned long base "  ","
.BI "struct ldmdb *ldb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
Partition check state including device holding the LDM Database
.IP "base" 12
Offset, into \fIstate->bdev\fP, of the database
.IP "ldb" 12
Cache of the database structures
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find and compare the four tables of contents of the LDM Database stored on
\fIstate->bdev\fP and return the parsed information into \fItoc1\fP.

The offsets and sizes of the configs are range-checked against a privhead.
.SH "RETURN"
'true'   \fItoc1\fP contains validated TOCBLOCK info
'false'  \fItoc1\fP contents are undefined
